taskDescription:
Determine if sets <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow>
  <mi>A</mi>
</mrow><annotation encoding="LaTeX">A</annotation></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow>
  <mi>B</mi>
</mrow><annotation encoding="LaTeX">B</annotation></semantics></math> are equal, equivalent, or neither: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow>
  <mi>A</mi>
  <mo>=</mo>
  <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>
  <mi>a</mi>
  <mo>,</mo>
  <mi>b</mi>
  <mo>,</mo>
  <mi>c</mi>
  <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>
</mrow><annotation encoding="LaTeX">A = \{a, b,c\}</annotation></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow>
  <mi>B</mi>
  <mo>=</mo>
  <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">{</mo>
  <mi>c</mi>
  <mo>,</mo>
  <mi>a</mi>
  <mo>,</mo>
  <mi>b</mi>
  <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">}</mo>
</mrow><annotation encoding="LaTeX">B = \{c,a,b\}</annotation></semantics></math>.
